\nI've fixed my [fiddle](https:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/Aluvyer\/kbey3f9L\/11\/) by changing the image host and added a screenshot to my post. (edit)\r\n\r\n> I am not sure there is an example of that, so this post can be considered to be a request to create one.\r\n\r\nIndeed! An example would be very nice!\r\nI'll try applying the `customDistanceMaterial` to my Mesh.\r\n\r\nThank You for your attention!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-20T13:51:20.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560#issuecomment-309759848","id":309759848,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwOTc1OTg0OA==","updated_at":"2017-06-20T13:51:20.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/309759848","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/25798430?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/DiogoSlepetys","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI1Nzk4NDMw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"DiogoSlepetys","type":"User","id":25798430,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Now that the dev branch has been updated, i've added the `customDistanceMaterial`* and a `PointLight` to the cloth example, achieving the following result:\r\n\r\n<img src='https:\/\/i.imgur.com\/JzKzwXZ.png' \/>\r\n\r\nFrom [PR #11591](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11591):\r\n```\r\n\/\/ distance material * \r\n\tvar distanceShader = THREE.ShaderLib[ \"distanceRGBA\" ];\r\n\tvar duniforms = THREE.UniformsUtils.clone( distanceShader.uniforms );\r\n\tduniforms.alphaMap.value = clothTexture;\r\n\tobject.customDistanceMaterial = new THREE.ShaderMaterial( {\r\n\t\tdefines: {\r\n\t\t\t 'USE_SHADOWMAP': '',\r\n\t\t\t 'USE_ALPHAMAP': '',\r\n\t\t\t 'ALPHATEST': 0.5\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\tuniforms: duniforms,\r\n\t\t\tvertexShader: distanceShader.vertexShader,\r\n\t\t\tfragmentShader: distanceShader.fragmentShader,\r\n\t\t\tside: THREE.DoubleSide,\r\n\t\t} );\r\n```\r\nAlso had to add those lines: \r\n\r\n- If using the same texture for the alpha mapping:\r\n`clothTexture.premultiplyAlpha = true;`\r\n- And to have both sides casting shadows:\r\n`renderer.shadowMap.renderSingleSided = false;`\r\n\r\nI still have a few doubts about having a `Mesh` with multiple `customDepthMaterial` & `customDistanceMaterial`, meaning i wouldn't have to make endless draw calls if i wanted to have a different alphaMap for every quad on my geometry. But i'm unsure if it would make more sense opening a new issue since i couldn't find anything about it. Please let me know.\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks a lot!","created_at":"2017-06-28T00:54:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560#issuecomment-311526304","id":311526304,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTUyNjMwNA==","updated_at":"2017-06-28T00:55:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311526304","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/25798430?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/DiogoSlepetys","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI1Nzk4NDMw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"DiogoSlepetys","type":"User","id":25798430,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/DiogoSlepetys\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">If using the same texture for the alpha mapping: clothTexture.premultiplyAlpha = true;\r\n\r\nIf your mesh has a transparent map, then you should use this pattern, instead\r\n```\r\nduniforms.map.value = clothTexture;\r\nobject.customDistanceMaterial = new THREE.ShaderMaterial( {\r\n\tdefines: {\r\n\t\t'USE_SHADOWMAP': '',\r\n\t\t'USE_MAP': '',\r\n\t\t'ALPHATEST': 0.5\r\n\t},\r\n```\r\nI do not think setting `clothTexture.premultiplyAlpha = true;` should be required.\r\n\r\n>And to have both sides casting shadows: renderer.shadowMap.renderSingleSided = false;\r\n\r\nYes. I'll add that to the existing example. Thanks.","created_at":"2017-06-28T01:26:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560#issuecomment-311530804","id":311530804,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11560","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxMTUzMDgwNA==","updated_at":"2017-06-28T01:26:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/311530804","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\